    "In the ANN literature 59, 61, 62, a method to tackle the problem of vanishing-or-exploding gradients at initialization is to make sure that the largest eigenvalues of the Jacobian are close to 1 in absolute value.",
    "Following classical work in the field of ANNs, we assume that M (n-1) has a small impact on the distribution of the eigenvalues of dt ðnÞ dt ðnÀ1Þ 61,62",
    "With this assumption, the focus in a standard ReLU network is just on the largest eigenvalue of the weight matrix w (n)61,62.",
    "However, in the case of a TTFS network, a new problem arises due to the fact that the weight matrix W (n) is multiplied by 1/B (n); see Eq.",
    "Therefore, the eigenvalues of the Jacobian dt ðnÞ dt ðnÀ1Þ are strongly determined by the diagonal matrix B (n) and not only by the weight matrix W (n) of the SNN."
  ],
